population.name: Study Population
population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of intranasal esketamine plus an oral antidepressant compared with an oral antidepressant plus intranasal placebo in delaying relapse of depressive symptoms in subjects with treatment-resistant depression (TRD) who are in stable remission after an initial period of treatment with intranasal esketamine plus an oral antidepressant.

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the efficacy of intranasal esketamine plus an oral antidepressant compared with an oral antidepressant plus intranasal placebo in delaying relapse of depressive symptoms in subjects with TRD who are in stable response (but not stable remission) after an initial period of treatment with intranasal esketamine plus an oral antidepressant.

objectives.name: Secondary Safety Objective
objectives.text: To assess the long-term safety and tolerability of intranasal esketamine plus an oral antidepressant in subjects with TRD, including: Treatment-emergent adverse events (TEAEs), including AEs of special interest; Effects on heart rate and blood pressure; Effects on respiratory rate and pulse oximetry; Sensory-perceptual changes (eg, dissociation); Potential for treatment-emergent psychotic symptoms; Cognitive effects; Effects on mood (eg, induction of mania or hypomania); Potential for suicidal ideation and behavior; Potential for treatment-emergent cystitis and other urinary tract symptoms; Potential for withdrawal and rebound symptoms following esketamine discontinuation; Nasal tolerability.

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Time to relapse (for subjects in stable remission) during the maintenance phase.

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Time to relapse (for subjects in stable response) during the maintenance phase.

endpoints.name: Secondary Safety Endpoints
endpoints.text: Incidence of TEAEs, changes in vital signs, Clinician-Administered Dissociative States Scale (CADSS), Brief Psychiatric Rating Scale (BPRS), Cogstate computerized cognitive battery, Young Mania Rating Scale (YMRS), Columbia-Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS), and nasal tolerability assessments.

exits.name: Optimization Ineligibility
exits.description: Misses >=21 days of oral antidepressant or >=3 MADRS assessments in first 8 weeks of optimization

exits.name: Study Termination for Efficacy
exits.description: Study stops once 84 relapses occur in stable remission subjects or based on interim analysis

exits.name: Transition to Safety Extension
exits.description: Eligible subjects may proceed to study 54135419TRD3008 after Early Withdrawal/End of Maintenance visit

notes.text: a) An additional, optional period of up to 3 weeks is permitted to taper and discontinue all current medication(s) being used for depression after completion of the Week 4 (Visit 1.3) assessments.

b) If a subject withdraws before the end of the open-label induction phase (ie, before completing Visit 2.9/Day 28) for reasons other than withdrawal of consent, an Early Withdrawal Visit should be conducted.
c) Predose (if/when performed on intranasal dosing days).
d) Clinic visits (visit window +/- 3 days) will be conducted for all intranasal treatment sessions.
e) Performed only at clinic visits for intranasal treatment sessions (omitted if remote MADRS only).
f) Predose (if/when performed on intranasal dosing days). Predose subject-reported outcome assessments should be administered before all other study-related procedures during a clinic visit.
g) Postdose vital signs will be performed at t = +40 minutes, 1 hour, and 1.5 hours postdose.
h) The 12-lead electrocardiogram will be performed at 1 hour postdose.
i) The MOAA/S will be performed every 15 minutes from predose to t = 1.5 hours postdose.
j) The BPRS+ and CADSS will be performed predose and at 40 minutes and 1.5 hours postdose.
k) CGADR will be performed at 1 hour and 1.5 hours postdose.
l) The nasal symptom questionnaire will be performed predose and at 1 hour postdose.
m) Blood samples should be collected prior to dosing.
n) Additional 2-week supply of the oral antidepressant medication only for subjects entering the follow-up phase.
o) Only applicable to women with a menstrual cycle.
p) If the subject has significant nasal congestion on the day of a scheduled assessment of sense of smell, then the site should consider postponing the UPSIT or Smell Threshold Test.

q) If a subject has started a scheduled clinic visit in which an intranasal treatment session is planned, but then a predose observation prompts the site staff to postpone the intranasal treatment session, then all time points of the footnoted assessments must be repeated on the actual intranasal treatment session day.
r) Drug accountability for intranasal study medication should be performed weekly during Weeks 5 through 8 and then weekly or every other week from Weeks 9 through 15.

analysisPopulations.name: All Enrolled Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The All Enrolled analysis set includes all subjects who sign the informed consent form.
analysisPopulations.label: All Enrolled
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The All Enrolled analysis set includes all subjects who sign the informed consent form.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least 1 dose of intranasal study medication and at least 1 dose of oral antidepressant during the maintenance phase. Transferred-entry subjects who continue to receive an oral antidepressant plus intranasal placebo will not be included in the full analysis sets.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least 1 dose of intranasal study medication and at least 1 dose of oral antidepressant during the maintenance phase. Transferred-entry subjects who continue to receive an oral antidepressant plus intranasal placebo will not be included in the full analysis sets.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose of intranasal study medication AND received >=1 dose of oral antidepressant during maintenance phase

analysisPopulations.name: Interim Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The interim Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least 1 dose of intranasal study medication and at least 1 dose of oral antidepressant during the maintenance phase and were randomized at least 22 weeks before the interim data cut-off date.
analysisPopulations.label: Interim FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The interim Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least 1 dose of intranasal study medication and at least 1 dose of oral antidepressant during the maintenance phase and were randomized at least 22 weeks before the interim data cut-off date.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose of intranasal study medication AND received >=1 dose of oral antidepressant AND randomized >=22 weeks before interim data cut-off

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The safety analysis set for a phase (e.g., induction, optimization, maintenance, or follow-up) includes all subjects who received at least 1 dose of intranasal study medication or 1 dose of oral antidepressant during that phase.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The safety analysis set for a phase (e.g., induction, optimization, maintenance, or follow-up) includes all subjects who received at least 1 dose of intranasal study medication or 1 dose of oral antidepressant during that phase.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received >=1 dose of intranasal study medication OR >=1 dose of oral antidepressant during the specific phase

analysisPopulations.name: Follow-up Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The follow-up analysis set includes all subjects who enter the follow-up phase.
analysisPopulations.label: FU Set
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The follow-up analysis set includes all subjects who enter the follow-up phase.

titles.text: A Randomized, Double-blind, Multicenter, Active-controlled Study of Intranasal Esketamine Plus an Oral Antidepressant for Relapse Prevention in Treatment-resistant Depression
Sustenance of Esketamine Treatment Response With Repeated Doses at Intervals Determined by Symptom Severity

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Treatment-resistant depression definition
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Treatment-resistant depression is defined as a lack of clinically meaningful improvement after treatment with at least 2 different antidepressant agents prescribed in adequate doses for adequate duration. The upper limit of 5 antidepressants is only applicable to the past 2 years of a current episode of depression in cases where the current episode is >2 years.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Nonresponse improvement threshold
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Nonresponse defined as 25% improvement per Massachusetts General Hospital - Antidepressant Treatment Response Questionnaire (MGH-ATRQ), which specifies at least 6 weeks of treatment at a minimum therapeutic dose.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Site Independent Qualification Assessment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Site Independent Qualification Assessment confirms the subject's current major depressive episode, antidepressant treatment response in the current depressive episode, and severity of depression (required at Week 1 to be MADRS total score 28).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Thyroid function requirements
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: If the thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) value is outside the normal reference range, then the free thyroxine (FT4) level will be assessed. If the FT4 level is normal, then the subject can be enrolled. If the FT4 level is outside the normal reference range, then the subject is not eligible.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Contraceptive requirements
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Contraceptive use by men or women should be consistent with local regulations regarding the use of contraceptive methods for subjects participating in clinical studies. Includes strengthened definitions of women who are not of childbearing potential and requirements for highly effective methods of contraception.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Transferred-entry subject alignment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Transferred-entry subjects must meet the same criteria at the point of entry to this study as the direct-entry subjects at the same time point (ie, beginning of optimization phase).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Severe renal impairment exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Exclude subjects with severe renal impairment (creatinine clearance <30 mL/min).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Transferred-entry exclusion alignment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Transferred-entry subjects must meet none of the exclusion criteria applicable to direct-entry subjects at the beginning of the optimization phase.

conditions.name: Induction Response
conditions.description: Criteria to proceed from Induction to Optimization
conditions.text: >=50% reduction in MADRS total score from baseline (Day 1) to end of Week 4

conditions.name: Stable Remission
conditions.description: Criteria for primary efficacy randomization in Maintenance
conditions.text: MADRS <=12 for at least 3 of the last 4 weeks of optimization; Weeks 15 and 16 must be <=12

conditions.name: Stable Response
conditions.description: Criteria for secondary efficacy randomization in Maintenance
conditions.text: >=50% reduction in MADRS from baseline in each of the last 2 weeks of optimization, but not in stable remission

conditions.name: Relapse Criteria
conditions.text: MADRS >=22 for 2 consecutive assessments 5-15 days apart, or hospitalization for worsening depression/suicidality

study.name: A Randomized, Double-blind, Multicenter, Active-controlled Study of Intranasal Esketamine Plus an Oral Antidepressant for Relapse Prevention in Treatment-resistant Depression

substances.name: Esketamine
substances.description: S-enantiomer of ketamine; NMDA receptor antagonist

transitionRules.name: Screening to Induction
transitionRules.text: Non-responders to current antidepressant (<=25% improvement in MADRS) with MADRS >=28 at Weeks 2 and 4

transitionRules.name: Induction Dose Modification
transitionRules.text: Dose may be adjusted between 56mg and 84mg on Days 4, 8, 11, 15, 18, and 22 based on efficacy and tolerability

transitionRules.name: Maintenance Frequency Adjustment
transitionRules.text: Frequency individualized to weekly or every other week; max 3 switches from weekly to every other week

transitionRules.name: Safety Discontinuation - ECG
transitionRules.text: QTcF change from baseline >=60 msec and QTcF >480 msec, or QTcF >500 msec

transitionRules.name: Safety Discontinuation - Bladder
transitionRules.text: Confirmed diagnosis of ulcerative cystitis requires immediate discontinuation

commentAnnotations.text: Janssen Research & Development is a global organization that operates through different legal entities in various countries.
The justification for allowing a single excursion of the MADRS total score or one missed MADRS assessment was made on the basis that it could be due to a life event and not the underlying illness.
Benzodiazepine rescue medication is permitted only post-dose on the dosing day.
If the Early Withdrawal Visit is conducted on the same day as a scheduled visit, duplicate assessments are not required.

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Substantial amendment updating safety precautions and eligibility criteria
Substantial amendment to improve recruitment and revise entry criteria
Substantial amendment revising stable remission criteria and study stop rules

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Revised stable remission criteria to allow for a single excursion or missing assessment at specific weeks.
Removed the eligibility restriction regarding missed MADRS assessments during the first 8 weeks of the optimization phase.
Removed the provision to stop the study for futility based on interim analysis results.
Revised antidepressant treatment requirements at study entry and non-response definitions to improve recruitment.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: To enhance the number of clinically valid subjects proceeding to the Maintenance phase as stable remitters.
Potential outcome of placebo arm being as good as treatment arm may inform long-term use rather than indicating futility.
Clonidine is considered a safe and effective treatment option for blood pressure elevation.
Based on feedback received from Investigators to improve recruitment.

studyChanges.beforeText: MADRS total score 12 for the last 4 weeks of the optimization phase
studyChanges.afterText: MADRS total score 12 for at least 3 of the last 4 weeks of the optimization phase, but one excursion of a MADRS total score >12 or one missing MADRS assessment is permitted at Optimization week 13 or 14 only. The MADRS total score at weeks 15 and 16 must be 12.
studyChanges.summary: Modified stable remission definition to allow for limited excursions.

studyChanges.beforeText: If 3 MADRS assessments are missed during the first 8 weeks of the optimization phase (Week 5 to Week 12), the subject can complete the optimization phase but is not eligible to participate in the maintenance phase.
studyChanges.summary: Removed restriction on missed MADRS assessments for maintenance phase eligibility.

studyChanges.beforeText: On Days 18, 22, and 25, the dose must remain stable (unchanged).
studyChanges.afterText: On Days 18, 22, and 25, a dose reduction from 84 mg to 56 mg is permitted if required for tolerability; no dose increase is permitted.
studyChanges.summary: Permitted dose reductions for tolerability on specific induction days.

studyChanges.beforeText: Evidence of 2nd and 3rd degree AV block, or 1st degree AV block with PR interval >200 msec
studyChanges.afterText: Evidence of 2nd and 3rd degree AV block
studyChanges.summary: Deleted exclusion for 1st degree AV block as esketamine showed no impact on PR interval.
